  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (human-error gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Clinician perfusionist operates the pump at the bedside; however, no operator use-error modes, misuse scenarios, or training-gap effects are characterized anywhere in the validation program. All validation experiments and simulation runs assume correctly formatted boundary conditions and nominal user inputs throughout.",
